OL,3,CBoy, 16, fled police and caused crash
OL,4,Cwhich left woman with brain bleed
OL,6,FHe pleaded guilty to causing serious
OL,7,Finjury by dangerous driving and was
OL,8,Fjailed for 18 months during a hearing
OL,9,Fat Exeter Crown Court.
OL,11,FThe court heard he did not have a
OL,12,Flicence or insurance at the time of
OL,13,Fthe offence and was over the
OL,14,Fprescribed limit for cannabis.
OL,16,FSergeant Troy Bennett from the Serious
OL,17,FCollision Investigation Team said:
OL,18,F"James Forrest-Hazell was 16 years of
OL,19,Fage at the time of the offence and he
OL,20,Fshould never have been behind the
OL,21,Fwheel of a car in the first place.
